data.name: Pork Combo Chop with Honey Mustard Glaze and Roasted Vegetables
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy pork chops glazed with a sweet and tangy honey mustard sauce, paired with colorful roasted vegetables for a delightful, healthy meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a small bowl, mix honey and Dijon mustard to create the glaze.
Place the pork chops in a baking dish and brush both sides with the honey mustard glaze.
In another bowl, toss the sliced carrots, bell peppers, and zucchini with olive oil, garlic powder, thyme, salt, and pepper.
Spread the vegetables around the pork chops in the baking dish.
Bake in the preheated oven for about 25-30 minutes, or until the pork is cooked through and the vegetables are tender.
Serve hot, drizzled with any remaining honey mustard glaze.
